A labor of love, given freely: use it, learn from it, self-host it, build your own creative visions on it. Run it as a network service and the AGPL has you share your changes back, so it stays a commons. It is NOT for sale, and NOT to be resold as a SaaS.

This is the LOCAL render backend: it runs on YOUR own hardware (your own GPU), under your control. Skyphusion Labs hosts nothing, operates nothing, and runs no instance of this for anyone. There is no service here that collects your data, because there is no service: your prompts, images, models, and finished renders stay on your machine. By architecture, your data never leaves your box.
